article.headline: UTEP 60, Texas-Pan American 42
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Stefon Jackson scored 17 points and grabbed eight rebounds to lead Texas-El Paso to a 60-42 victory over Texas-Pan American on Friday night. Gabriel McCulley and Arnett Moultrie were the only other players to score in double digits for the Miners (8-5) with 13 and 10 points, respectively. Two players scored in double figures for Texas-Pan American (4-9). Nick Weiermiller scored 16 and Emmanuel Jones added 10. The Miners outscored the Broncs in the paint, 32-18.
